			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd would really like to know what SOE does when they patch that takes 7-8 hours. I used to be an administrator on a good size Windows NT Terminal Server farm (before I started my own business, went bankrupt, and destroyed my life) and I never did any patches or updates that took over an hour including reboots. 
<br />

<br />
I suppose their systems aren't 100% redundant so maybe they're backing something up. Seven hours seems a bit extreme though. Given their habit of having to do emergency patchs one might think they are doing their patch testing after they roll out the code. I, in the real world, would have been beheaded for standard emergency downtime after every patch. 
<br />

<br />
I'm not trying to rant  but I would really like to know what their lengthy patch process involves.<br />_________________<br />"I feel good, and I'm not scared at all. I just feel kind of... kind of invincible... Is it getting hot in here, or is it just me?"
<br />

<br />
Seker Anhur
<br />
58 Mage - Zebuxoruk</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
